title: Perfect Grilled Side Dish   Baked Beans
description: My other name for this is the ‘Perfect Grilled Food Side-Dish.’ Plus you can make them in advance and just reheat when you need them.  And whatever you do, be sure to keep in the chipotles as they add a beautiful smokiness.

transcripts:
There are food combinations that just naturally go together. Bread and butter, wine and cheese, and soup and salad. But one of my favorite combinations is anything BBQ and baked beans. cook diced bacon in an oven proof pot until not quite crispy. Remove most of the grease and then add diced onion and diced green pepper. Let soften for about five minutes.

Add maple favored beans, chilli sauce, worcestershire,  yellow mustard, cumen, minced chipotle peppers, and Kosher salt. Then just stir well, cover, and bake in a 350 oven for about an hour. And then just lift the lid and rejoice. But if you felt like putting them with some ribs, a little chicken or even a bratwurst, well they'd be even better.
